Over the weekend, the Treasury Secretary and the National Economic Council Director worked with banking regulators to address issues at Silicon Valley Bank and Signature Bank. They were able to find a solution that protects American workers and small businesses, as well as ensuring the safety of the financial system. Importantly, this solution also ensures that taxpayer dollars are not put at risk. The article mentions that people and businesses can have confidence that their bank deposits will be secure. The author emphasizes their commitment to holding those responsible for the problems accountable and to continuing efforts to strengthen oversight and regulation of larger banks. The article concludes by mentioning that the author will deliver remarks the next day on maintaining a resilient banking system to protect the economic recovery.